assesmentMethods.en:
The assessment of the case analysis is based on the following criteria: 

1) whether the analysis described the case comprehensively and the different emphases of different court instances were highlighted; 

2) whether sources of law relevant to the case were comprehensively addressed; 

3) whether the analysis weighed different legal arguments;

4) how persuasive the legal arguments presented in the analysis were; 

5) grammar, writing style and technical finish.

The assessment also considers the student’s presentation at seminar, performance as an opponent, active participation in discussions, and adherence to schedules.

